text: The Chüemettler () is a mountain of the Appenzell Alps, overlooking the Walensee in the canton of St. Gallen. It lies south of the Speer and southeast of the Federispitz mountains. Chüe literally means cows in Swiss-German language, Mettler is a family name respectively a term used as name of several local areas. ==References== ==External links== * Chüemettler on hikr.org Category:Mountains of Switzerland Category:Mountains of the canton of St. Gallen Category:Mountains of the Alps Category:Appenzell Alps
